data.name: BazykinModel_description
data.value: The predator-prey model by A. D. Bazykin, in contrast to the Lotka-Volterra model, takes into account additional factors affecting real predator-prey systems: the nonlinearity of the reproduction rate of the victim and competition within its population, the effect of saturation of the predator with the victim, competition of predators for victims, the nonlinear nature of the destruction of the victim by the predator and other effects.

data.name: PlotType_phase_description
data.value: A single curve where each point represents the size of the prey (X axis) and predator (Y axis) population at a certain point in time.

data.name: PlotType_time_description
data.value: The change in the populations of prey and predators over time is displayed as two independent curves on a two-dimensional plane, where time corresponds to the X axis and the population size corresponds to the Y axis.

data.name: About_text
data.value: Population dynamics simulation with A. D. Bazykin "prey-predator" models.
